Barcelona captain Carles Puyol back training after knee surgery
Barcelona captain Carles Puyol has returned to training with the Spanish champions after missing the past six months with a knee injury."The team is getting its captain back and we have the centre-back we wanted," said Barca coach Gerardo Martino.Spain defender Puyol, 35,had keyhole surgery on his right knee in March- his second operation in 11 months.Martino prioritised signing a centre-back over the summer, butfailed with a bid for Chelsea's David Luiz.Puyol initially trained on his own on Friday, before joining the rest of his team-mates for the final part of the training session.